Amen.

43
00:03:15,132 --> 00:03:17,726
- Let's kill 'em all.
- (all) Hu-ah!

44
00:03:25,852 --> 00:03:26,602
You all right, Boylar?

45
00:03:28,452 --> 00:03:30,249
Hell, yeah.

46
00:03:30,452 --> 00:03:33,046
- Let's heat 'em up, Nat.
- See you in Baghdad.

47
00:03:33,332 --> 00:03:34,924
Yes, sir.

48
00:03:35,012 --> 00:03:36,923
(engines starting)

49
00:03:57,052 --> 00:03:58,485
Battle-carry Sabot.

50
00:04:00,132 --> 00:04:02,009
Sabot bullet coming up, sir.

51
00:04:06,892 --> 00:04:08,291
- Sabot loaded.
- Indexed.

52
00:04:08,372 --> 00:04:09,088
Crew report.

53
00:04:09,172 --> 00:04:10,685
- Driver ready.
- Loader ready.

54
00:04:10,772 --> 00:04:13,161
Gunner ready to give Saddam
a new way to hurt.

55
00:04:13,252 --> 00:04:14,128
- Hu-ah!
- Hu-ah!

56
00:04:14,212 --> 00:04:15,122
Hu-ah.

57
00:04:16,532 --> 00:04:17,726
All right, Boylar?

58
00:04:17,812 --> 00:04:18,881
Roger that.

59
00:04:18,972 --> 00:04:21,884
All Cougar elements, this is Cougar-6.
Report Red Con 1. Over.

60
00:04:27,252 --> 00:04:30,608
All Sabre elements, this is Sabre-6.

61
00:04:30,692 --> 00:04:31,568
Move out.

62
00:04:55,012 --> 00:04:56,809
(radio chatter)

63
00:04:58,852 --> 00:05:00,968
Sabre-6, this is Cougar-6.

64
00:05:01,052 --> 00:05:02,405
No joy over here.

65
00:05:02,492 --> 00:05:04,608
Permission to try an alternate route. Over.

66
00:05:04,692 --> 00:05:07,809
Roger that, Cougar-6.
Work your way to phase line hammer.

67
00:05:07,892 --> 00:05:10,360
- (Nat) No surprises. Copy?
- Roger that.

68
00:05:10,452 --> 00:05:13,524
I'm taking up the right flank.
I’ll get back to you. Out.

69
00:05:17,812 --> 00:05:21,009
Contact. I see flashes, 3,500 metres, sir.

70
00:05:21,092 --> 00:05:23,526
- All right.
- Hold on. They got no range.

71
00:05:27,612 --> 00:05:28,886
2,500 metres and closing, sir.

72
00:05:28,972 --> 00:05:30,485
Ready to lase and blaze.

73
00:05:31,772 --> 00:05:33,171
Contact, sir. He's in range.

74
00:05:33,252 --> 00:05:35,561
- Come on, let me kill his ass.
- Fire!

75
00:05:35,732 --> 00:05:36,847
On the way!

76
00:05:41,972 --> 00:05:42,961
Yeah! Yeah!

77
00:05:43,052 --> 00:05:44,644
Yeah, yeah, yeah!

78
00:05:44,732 --> 00:05:47,326
- Find me another target, Patella.
- Loaded!

79
00:05:47,412 --> 00:05:49,084
- Identified.
- Fire.

80
00:05:56,372 --> 00:05:56,963
Fire!

81
00:06:05,852 --> 00:06:07,922
(Patella) Got him! We got him!

82
00:06:08,012 --> 00:06:09,491
Sabre-6, Liberty-6.

83
00:06:09,572 --> 00:06:11,528
We got enemy tangos retreating...

84
00:06:11,612 --> 00:06:13,921
..vicinity grid 2-4-9er-8.

85
00:06:14,012 --> 00:06:17,243
Your pursuit should intercept
their retreat, grid 7-6-5.

86
00:06:18,332 --> 00:06:19,890
Roger that, Liberty-6.

87
00:06:19,972 --> 00:06:21,963
- Troops!
- Troops!

88
00:06:40,772 --> 00:06:42,410
Cease fire! Cease fire!

89
00:06:48,692 --> 00:06:51,445
(shouting in Arabic)

90
00:06:51,532 --> 00:06:52,931
Come on! Come on!

91
00:06:56,052 --> 00:06:57,371
Sabre-6, this is Cougar-6.

92
00:06:57,452 --> 00:06:58,601
Go ahead, Cougar-6.

93
00:06:58,692 --> 00:07:00,967
I have got mines. Repeat, mines.

94
00:07:01,052 --> 00:07:02,690
I gotta get the fuck out of here.

95
00:07:02,772 --> 00:07:05,127
(Nat) Work your way to gridline Charlie.

96
00:07:05,212 --> 00:07:08,966
Cougar-6 to all Cougar elements.
Let's get the hell out of here.

97
00:07:12,092 --> 00:07:14,208
(shouting in Arabic)

98
00:07:29,572 --> 00:07:31,085
Whoa! What the...

99
00:07:31,212 --> 00:07:32,884
Oh, shit!

100
00:07:32,972 --> 00:07:35,042
All Sabre units, this is Sabre-6.

101
00:07:35,132 --> 00:07:37,851
We just lost a tank.
Anybody see the shooter?

102
00:07:37,932 --> 00:07:40,446
- I didn't see anything.
- Where they coming from?

103
00:07:41,572 --> 00:07:43,324
Who the hell is shooting at us?

104
00:07:43,412 --> 00:07:44,845
Liberty-6, we got enemy tanks...

105
00:07:44,932 --> 00:07:46,684
..retreating grid 7-6...

106
00:07:46,772 --> 00:07:48,842
- Patella, that one of our tanks?
- Hard to tell.

107
00:07:48,932 --> 00:07:50,160
Make it out, and fast!

108
00:07:51,572 --> 00:07:54,132
Oh, shit! We're almost browning out.

109
00:07:54,212 --> 00:07:55,691
Nat, what's happening?

110
00:07:55,772 --> 00:07:58,650
Liberty-6, we got enemy tanks on our flank.
We have contact.

111
00:07:58,732 --> 00:07:59,687
This is Cougar-6.

112
00:07:59,772 --> 00:08:02,445
Enemy tangos at phase line delta. Over.

113
00:08:02,532 --> 00:08:04,568
- Patella, find me a target.
- I think I got one, sir.

114
00:08:04,652 --> 00:08:06,370
Do you or do you not have a target?

115
00:08:06,452 --> 00:08:07,248
I think so!

116
00:08:07,332 --> 00:08:08,401
Gunner, Sabot, tank.

117
00:08:08,492 --> 00:08:09,447
Identify! Up!

118
00:08:09,532 --> 00:08:10,521
Fire!

119
00:08:12,652 --> 00:08:14,085
He just fired, sir.

120
00:08:14,172 --> 00:08:15,207
They're firing at us!

121
00:08:15,292 --> 00:08:17,601
- Loader!
- Up, sir!

122
00:08:17,772 --> 00:08:18,602
Fire!

123
00:08:21,812 --> 00:08:23,086
Yeah! That's the one!

124
00:08:23,172 --> 00:08:24,127
All right.

125
00:08:24,212 --> 00:08:26,601
(radio) Sabre-6, we just lost Cougar-6.

126
00:08:26,772 --> 00:08:28,683
- We got him.
- Sabre, you just lit up a friendly!

127
00:08:28,772 --> 00:08:30,091
I heard you! We... what?

128
00:08:30,172 --> 00:08:31,571
Oh, my God.

129
00:08:31,652 --> 00:08:33,847
You just lit up Boylar, goddamn it!

130
00:08:33,932 --> 00:08:36,526
(radio) Sabre-6, Nat, what's happening?

131
00:08:36,612 --> 00:08:38,011
Patella, was that one of our tanks?

132
00:08:38,092 --> 00:08:40,162
He fired, sir.

133
00:08:40,252 --> 00:08:42,083
At us or at the T-72s?

134
00:08:42,172 --> 00:08:43,082
I don't know.

135
00:08:43,172 --> 00:08:45,402
At us or at the T-72s?

136
00:08:45,492 --> 00:08:46,607
I don't know!

137
00:08:46,692 --> 00:08:48,648
(Patella) Oh, Jesus fucking Christ.

138
00:08:48,732 --> 00:08:51,007
(radio) Colonel Serling, report status now.

139
00:08:51,092 --> 00:08:52,491
(explosion)

140
00:08:53,492 --> 00:08:55,130
They have range on us, sir.

141
00:08:55,212 --> 00:08:57,203
Sir!

142
00:09:19,852 --> 00:09:21,524
Oh, Christ, Colonel...

143
00:09:25,612 --> 00:09:28,206
I gave the order to fire.

144
00:09:51,692 --> 00:09:53,330
So with your thermal equipment,...

145
00:09:53,412 --> 00:09:57,166
..confused by burning tanks
and smoke obscuring your visual ID,...

146
00:09:57,252 --> 00:10:01,609
..you couldn't tell the difference
between the T-54 and the Abrams.

147
00:10:01,692 --> 00:10:03,523
I believe that, uh, we...

148
00:10:03,612 --> 00:10:06,001
l should have known the difference,...

149
00:10:06,092 --> 00:10:09,289
..even with the night scope.

150
00:10:09,372 --> 00:10:11,408
If we weren't under attack,...

151
00:10:11,492 --> 00:10:16,361
But, under the circumstances,
there was no way to tell the difference.

152
00:10:19,172 --> 00:10:20,605
Under the circumstances,...

153
00:10:20,692 --> 00:10:23,001
..I suppose there was
no way to tell the difference, but...

154
00:10:23,092 --> 00:10:24,810
There was no way to tell the difference.

155
00:10:24,892 --> 00:10:26,086
Thank you, Colonel.

156
00:10:26,852 --> 00:10:28,251
That's all we need.

157
00:11:03,652 --> 00:11:05,563
(Patella) We’re almost browning out!

158
00:11:05,652 --> 00:11:09,804
(Boylar) We got enemy tanks on our flank.
We have contact.

159
00:11:09,892 --> 00:11:11,120
Aah!

160
00:11:11,212 --> 00:11:12,804
We just lost Cougar-6!

161
00:11:12,892 --> 00:11:15,042
You just lit up a friendly!

162
00:11:15,132 --> 00:11:16,121
(knock on door)

163
00:11:16,212 --> 00:11:17,201
Colonel Serling?

164
00:11:17,292 --> 00:11:18,202
Yes.

165
00:11:18,292 --> 00:11:20,647
You OK? Can I get you something?

166
00:11:20,732 --> 00:11:22,006
Yes, I'm fine. Fine.

167
00:11:22,092 --> 00:11:25,050
Uh, yes, you can get me a cup of coffee.

168
00:11:25,132 --> 00:11:26,360
You got it.

169
00:11:26,452 --> 00:11:29,489
We missed you and Meredith
at Banacek's party last night.

170
00:11:29,572 --> 00:11:32,006
I'm too old to dance with you youngsters.

171
00:11:32,092 --> 00:11:34,765
Meredith's not,
so tell her to come without you next time.

172
00:11:34,852 --> 00:11:36,843
Oh, OK. I willdo just that...

173
00:11:36,932 --> 00:11:37,842
..next time.

174
00:11:39,092 --> 00:11:40,810
(telephone rings)

175
00:11:40,892 --> 00:11:41,881
Colonel Serling.

176
00:11:41,972 --> 00:11:44,964
- Hershberg in five. Coffee's coming.
- Thanks.

177
00:11:45,052 --> 00:11:46,041
Yes.

178
00:11:50,452 --> 00:11:51,805
Washington Post?

179
00:11:53,692 --> 00:11:54,807
About?

180
00:11:56,852 --> 00:11:58,205
Yes, I was there.

181
00:11:58,292 --> 00:12:00,567
That's a matter of public record.

182
00:12:02,252 --> 00:12:04,925
Well, thank you very much, Mr...

183
00:12:05,012 --> 00:12:09,164
Gartner. Thank you, Mr Gartner,
but I have nothing to say.

184
00:12:09,252 --> 00:12:10,241
No, sir.

185
00:12:11,572 --> 00:12:12,561
No, sir!

186
00:12:14,052 --> 00:12:16,247
Well, I’ll do just that.

187
00:12:16,332 --> 00:12:17,447
Right.

188
00:12:22,532 --> 00:12:24,921
Colonel Serling's here, sir.

189
00:12:25,012 --> 00:12:25,967
Ban.

190
00:12:26,052 --> 00:12:29,727
I'm not talking to you.
Won't even come to my anniversary party?

191
00:12:29,812 --> 00:12:32,246
You and Sylvia have been together,
what, a month?

192
00:12:32,332 --> 00:12:35,768
The way she danced with that marine,
it won't last another week.

193
00:12:35,852 --> 00:12:37,763
It may be my last anniversary party.

194
00:12:38,052 --> 00:12:39,485
Were you there for me?

195
00:12:39,572 --> 00:12:41,210
What's up?

196
00:12:42,892 --> 00:12:43,927
Hey, Nat.

197
00:12:44,012 --> 00:12:45,764
I've got to talk to you.

198
00:12:45,852 --> 00:12:46,967
How we holding, Ban?

199
00:12:47,052 --> 00:12:48,280
Running late, sir.

200
00:12:48,372 --> 00:12:50,567
- May I run a few things by you, sir?
- Quickly.

201
00:12:50,652 --> 00:12:51,687
Lieutenant Boylar's parents...

202
00:12:51,772 --> 00:12:52,682
Boylar?

203
00:12:52,772 --> 00:12:55,684
Tom Boylar. He died in AI Bathra.

204
00:12:55,772 --> 00:12:57,251
He'd been with me a long time.

205
00:12:57,332 --> 00:13:00,130
- From Virginia, right?
- Roger that, sir.

206
00:13:00,212 --> 00:13:02,362
His parents have written to me.
They're hearing rumours.

207
00:13:02,452 --> 00:13:05,364
You know we can't discuss it.
You have to put them off.

208
00:13:05,452 --> 00:13:07,682
- Yes, sir, but...
- Tell them he died in action.

209
00:13:07,772 --> 00:13:11,367
- He's a hero. That's all they want to know.
- Roger, but it's not just his parents.

210
00:13:11,452 --> 00:13:12,567
We got a call...

211
00:13:12,652 --> 00:13:14,563
..from the Washington Post.

212
00:13:14,652 --> 00:13:15,880
A reporter named Gartner.

213
00:13:15,972 --> 00:13:17,405
A reporter called you about AI Bathra?

214
00:13:17,492 --> 00:13:18,607
You didn't talk?

215
00:13:18,692 --> 00:13:19,602
Of course not.

216
00:13:19,692 --> 00:13:22,411
Nobody ’ll hang you out to dry.
I won't let 'em.

217
00:13:22,492 --> 00:13:23,720
Did you listen to the tape, sir?

218
00:13:23,932 --> 00:13:25,251
Colonel, the war's over.

219
00:13:25,332 --> 00:13:29,245
You and I have been given
the great responsiblility and privllege...

220
00:13:29,332 --> 00:13:32,165
..of investigating combat medals
for our army.

221
00:13:32,252 --> 00:13:34,402
In other words, we've been passed over.

222
00:13:34,532 --> 00:13:37,410
I prefer to think of it
as a second chance, Nat.

223
00:13:37,492 --> 00:13:39,448
We understand each other?

224
00:13:39,532 --> 00:13:40,487
Yes, sir.

225
00:13:40,572 --> 00:13:41,971
OK.

226
00:13:42,052 --> 00:13:46,409
The White House heard we're considering
the Medal of Honour for a chopper pllot...

227
00:13:46,492 --> 00:13:48,005
..who saved some guys
on a downed Blackhawk.

228
00:13:48,092 --> 00:13:50,970
- Naturally they want it for Veterans Day.
- Naturally.

229
00:13:51,052 --> 00:13:53,964
Which is why
you're taking over the inquiry.

230
00:13:54,052 --> 00:13:57,647
We've got the rescued soldiers
in there for debriefing.

231
00:13:59,492 --> 00:14:00,971
Attention.

232
00:14:02,092 --> 00:14:04,003
Morning. Take your seats.

233
00:14:04,092 --> 00:14:05,207
Everything in order?

234
00:14:05,292 --> 00:14:09,729
- Just going over the sequence of events.
- Bring Colonel Serling up to speed.

235
00:14:09,812 --> 00:14:10,722
Morning, sir.

236
00:14:10,812 --> 00:14:12,086
Good to see you again.

237
00:14:12,172 --> 00:14:14,447
Could we get a picture
of you and the survivors?

238
00:14:14,532 --> 00:14:16,011
No, thank you.

239
00:14:16,092 --> 00:14:18,367
- Keep me in the loop.
- Thank you, sir.

240
00:14:20,692 --> 00:14:22,603
- Morning.
- Morning.

241
00:14:22,692 --> 00:14:26,480
Doug Bruno, White House.
Do everything my way and we’ll be fine.

242
00:14:27,172 --> 00:14:28,446
Nat Serling.

243
00:14:28,532 --> 00:14:31,000
I’ll, uh, get out ofyour way.

244
00:14:33,252 --> 00:14:34,207
- Major.
- Sir.

245
00:14:34,292 --> 00:14:37,489
25 February,
these men were part of a refuelling convoy.

246
00:14:37,572 --> 00:14:40,928
Their Blackhawk was shot down
by an SA-7 west ofAI Kufan.

247
00:14:41,012 --> 00:14:44,084
Five seconds after it locked on,
we were down.

248
00:14:44,172 --> 00:14:47,847
- We didn't know what hit us.
- Our lines were surrounding them so fast,...

249
00:14:47,932 --> 00:14:50,162
..we got caught in a pocket of resistance.

250
00:14:50,252 --> 00:14:55,326
Iraqi ground troops on the ridge above
kept them completely pinned down.

251
00:14:55,412 --> 00:14:57,164
Did you discuss surrendering?

252
00:15:01,772 --> 00:15:03,569
Yes, sir, we did.

253
00:15:03,652 --> 00:15:05,847
We were all wounded one way or another.

254
00:15:05,932 --> 00:15:08,969
We weren't trained
for that kind of situation, sir.

255
00:15:09,052 --> 00:15:11,043
Don't have to make excuses to me.

256
00:15:11,132 --> 00:15:12,531
Go on, Sam.

257
00:15:12,612 --> 00:15:14,489
That's all we got so far, sir.

258
00:15:14,572 --> 00:15:16,130
OK.

259
00:15:16,212 --> 00:15:18,362
- Lieutenant Chelli.
- Yes, sir.

260
00:15:18,452 --> 00:15:22,525
Well,
as ifthings weren't bad enough already,...

261
00:15:22,612 --> 00:15:24,568
..one oftheir T-54s...

262
00:15:24,652 --> 00:15:28,247
..joins the ragheads up on the ridge.

263
00:15:28,332 --> 00:15:30,050
(tank engine)

264
00:15:33,292 --> 00:15:35,806
Incoming! Get down!

265
00:15:38,092 --> 00:15:42,643
That round
kills the medic, Relleno, Gerspach,...

266
00:15:42,732 --> 00:15:45,405
..and, uh, Egan here lost his leg.

267
00:15:45,492 --> 00:15:47,722
So we figure that's it. We're dead.

268
00:15:48,732 --> 00:15:50,450
But then we hear it.

269
00:15:50,532 --> 00:15:52,648
Nothing like the sound of an inbound Huey.

270
00:15:52,732 --> 00:15:53,881
(helicopter)

271
00:15:57,892 --> 00:15:59,166
Yeah!

272
00:15:59,252 --> 00:16:00,128
Yeah!

273
00:16:02,932 --> 00:16:04,843
(Serling) This Huey, didit take anyfire?

274
00:16:04,932 --> 00:16:05,967
Right offthe bat.

275
00:16:06,052 --> 00:16:09,886
But this time
when the Huey comes back, it returns fire.

276
00:16:09,972 --> 00:16:11,610
Ground troops go for cover.

277
00:16:11,772 --> 00:16:14,002
Then the Huey circles back over the tank...

278
00:16:14,092 --> 00:16:17,209
That's when
they threw something overboard.

279
00:16:17,292 --> 00:16:22,047
- Threw something, or something fell off?
- I couldn't tell, but the tank blew.

280
00:16:23,252 --> 00:16:24,526
Oh!

281
00:16:24,612 --> 00:16:25,840
Yeah!

282
00:16:25,932 --> 00:16:27,490
Man, did it ever blow!

283
00:16:28,932 --> 00:16:32,004
We, uh, we never did see
what knocked the Huey down.

284
00:16:35,092 --> 00:16:36,730
(explosion)

285
00:16:36,812 --> 00:16:38,803
We couldn't see the crash.

286
00:16:39,332 --> 00:16:42,642
That night we caught sporadic ground fire.

287
00:16:42,732 --> 00:16:46,088
The Huey was down below,
between us and the enemy,...

288
00:16:46,172 --> 00:16:48,208
..so they caught most of it.

289
00:16:48,292 --> 00:16:50,726
Any communications
between you and them?

290
00:16:50,812 --> 00:16:53,121
No, sir. As I said, our radio was wasted.

291
00:16:53,212 --> 00:16:55,521
Shouting just draws enemy fire.

292
00:16:55,612 --> 00:17:00,447
So the Iraqis,
they start to close in on the Huey...

293
00:17:00,532 --> 00:17:01,965
..under cover fire,...

294
00:17:02,052 --> 00:17:04,441
..and the Huey returns fire.

295
00:17:04,532 --> 00:17:08,320
We figure it's all over,
and that's when we hear the rescue team.

296
00:17:08,412 --> 00:17:09,845
Cobras, Hueys...

297
00:17:09,932 --> 00:17:12,002
And a big-ass A-10 Thunderbolt.

298
00:17:14,652 --> 00:17:16,768
I swear I never heard such a sweet sound.

299
00:17:16,852 --> 00:17:18,808
But now the fuckers are...

300
00:17:20,052 --> 00:17:21,451
I'm sorry, sir.

301
00:17:21,532 --> 00:17:24,046
The Iraqis are letting loose with all they got.

302
00:17:24,132 --> 00:17:26,885
- You were right the first time.
- (laughter)

303
00:17:28,212 --> 00:17:31,204
Plus the Huey crew is stillbanging away.

304
00:17:31,292 --> 00:17:34,045
We load our wounded aboard,...

305
00:17:34,132 --> 00:17:37,329
..and that's when
somebody decided to leave the dead.

306
00:17:37,412 --> 00:17:39,403
I guess it was the commander ofthe rescue.

307
00:17:39,492 --> 00:17:40,402
Mm-hmm.

308
00:17:40,492 --> 00:17:42,084
And this... Huey crew,...

309
00:17:42,172 --> 00:17:46,051
.they, uh, they returned fire
all through the final rescue?

310
00:17:46,132 --> 00:17:47,929
Yes, sir. I... I think so.

311
00:17:48,012 --> 00:17:50,401
I couldn't see much, though.

312
00:17:50,492 --> 00:17:51,402
I heard it.

313
00:17:51,492 --> 00:17:54,962
Nothing else sounds like an M-16.
Not no A-K or M-60.

314
00:17:55,052 --> 00:17:57,327
I heard it, too.

315
00:17:57,412 --> 00:18:02,440
The last thing we see is the Thunderbolt
dropping napalm on the downed choppers.

316
00:18:02,532 --> 00:18:05,569
I don't know if it was Captain Walden...

317
00:18:05,652 --> 00:18:08,041
..but that Huey...

318
00:18:08,132 --> 00:18:09,451
..saved our lives.

319
00:18:13,172 --> 00:18:14,571
It sure sounds like it.

320
00:18:17,852 --> 00:18:19,763
OK.

321
00:18:21,332 --> 00:18:24,722
Thank you for your help.
I’ll look over your statements.

322
00:18:24,812 --> 00:18:25,961
Thank you, sir.

323
00:18:26,052 --> 00:18:27,644
Thank you, Colonel.

324
00:18:27,732 --> 00:18:28,801
That’ll be all.

325
00:18:28,892 --> 00:18:30,803
- Got something for me?
- I do, sir.

326
00:18:30,892 --> 00:18:33,645
Walden's 201 file. Evaluation reports.

327
00:18:33,732 --> 00:18:36,485
You know I'm going to need
background on these guys.

328
00:18:36,572 --> 00:18:40,565
Make sure we don't have a wife-beater
or an illegal allen or gays.

329
00:18:40,652 --> 00:18:41,971
That’ll blow it.

330
00:18:42,052 --> 00:18:44,202
About this Congressional Medal of Honour.

331
00:18:44,292 --> 00:18:48,410
It's not the Congressional Medal of Honour.
It's just the Medal of Honour.

332
00:18:48,492 --> 00:18:49,607
Tell that to Congress.

333
00:18:49,692 --> 00:18:51,728
If Captain Walden wins this medal...

334
00:18:51,812 --> 00:18:54,121
You don't win it. You, uh, receive it.

335
00:18:54,212 --> 00:18:55,725
It's not a contest.

336
00:18:55,812 --> 00:18:58,372
But that is perfect. That is why I'm here.

337
00:18:58,452 --> 00:19:01,489
I'm not here
to get down your throat, make you crazy,...

338
00:19:01,572 --> 00:19:03,528
..take these facts and twist them.

339
00:19:03,612 --> 00:19:07,400
I just want to get these nuances out
of your head and to get it straight from you.

340
00:19:07,492 --> 00:19:09,847
- It's a woman.
- You didn't know?

341
00:19:09,932 --> 00:19:12,844
What did you think the hoopla was about?

342
00:19:12,932 --> 00:19:15,730
Banacek's got information
on three of Walden's men.

343
00:19:15,812 --> 00:19:20,010
- The crew chief we're still tracking.
- This is Captain Karen Emma Walden.

344
00:19:20,092 --> 00:19:25,530
She's the first woman ever to be nominated
for a Medal of Honour for combat.

345
00:19:25,612 --> 00:19:26,931
I mean, this is gold.

346
00:19:27,012 --> 00:19:28,365
It's gold.

347
00:19:28,732 --> 00:19:30,802
Unfortunately it's posthumous,...

348
00:19:30,892 --> 00:19:33,087
..but I've got her Little daughter.

349
00:19:33,172 --> 00:19:35,606
I got the President of the United States.

350
00:19:35,692 --> 00:19:37,887
It's all set in the Rose Garden.

351
00:19:37,972 --> 00:19:42,250
The President's going to lean down and
hang that ribbon round that pretty face.

352
00:19:42,332 --> 00:19:46,450
There is not going to be
a dry eye from Nashua to Sacramento.

353
00:19:46,532 --> 00:19:48,568
Excuse us.

354
00:19:55,412 --> 00:19:57,209
OK, it was 5 to 1,...

355
00:19:57,292 --> 00:19:59,044
..hook shot.

356
00:19:59,132 --> 00:20:01,282
Me and her are cheerleaders.

357
00:20:01,372 --> 00:20:04,648
- More mashed potatoes.
- (woman) Sorry, no more potatoes,...

358
00:20:04,732 --> 00:20:07,371
