359
00:20:07,452 --> 00:20:10,171
Aah!

360
00:20:10,252 --> 00:20:11,890
(Boylar) Aah!

361
00:20:11,972 --> 00:20:14,532
Daddy, can I have your mashed potatoes?

362
00:20:16,932 --> 00:20:18,206
Daddy?

363
00:20:18,292 --> 00:20:20,248
Sir?

364
00:20:20,372 --> 00:20:22,169
Can I have your mashed potatoes?

365
00:20:23,212 --> 00:20:25,123
M... Yeah. Sure.

366
00:20:25,212 --> 00:20:26,645
Yeah,...

367
00:20:26,732 --> 00:20:28,211
..soldier.

368
00:20:28,292 --> 00:20:29,407
You want 'em all?

369
00:20:29,492 --> 00:20:31,403
(telephone rings)

370
00:20:31,492 --> 00:20:32,641
That enough?

371
00:20:36,212 --> 00:20:37,122
More?

372
00:20:38,652 --> 00:20:39,562
Hello?

373
00:20:39,652 --> 00:20:41,529
Yes.

374
00:20:41,612 --> 00:20:43,807
Uh, who is calling, please?

375
00:20:43,892 --> 00:20:45,211
Just a minute.

376
00:20:46,932 --> 00:20:47,967
It's for you.

377
00:20:48,052 --> 00:20:48,962
Who is it?

378
00:20:49,052 --> 00:20:50,485
Somebody Gartner.

379
00:20:52,772 --> 00:20:54,842
Want some more peas?

380
00:21:31,012 --> 00:21:32,127
Excuse me.

381
00:21:45,292 --> 00:21:47,169
Where are you going?

382
00:21:47,252 --> 00:21:48,367
Fort Hood.

383
00:21:48,452 --> 00:21:52,491
General Hershberg's got me investigating
a Medal of Honour.

384
00:21:52,572 --> 00:21:54,449
It's a woman.

385
00:21:54,532 --> 00:21:56,045
Good for her.

386
00:21:57,132 --> 00:21:58,201
Posthumous.

387
00:21:58,292 --> 00:22:00,442
Too bad, but still good for her.

388
00:22:01,692 --> 00:22:03,648
Mmm. Too bad.

389
00:22:11,012 --> 00:22:14,368
You talk to the investigators today?

390
00:22:14,452 --> 00:22:15,441
Right.

391
00:22:17,812 --> 00:22:19,643
It's all right, isn't it, Nat?

392
00:22:20,932 --> 00:22:22,411
Yeah. Fine.

393
00:22:25,972 --> 00:22:27,690
How long are you gone for?

394
00:22:27,772 --> 00:22:29,205
Couple of days.

395
00:22:32,852 --> 00:22:34,968
Then why are you emptying
your sock drawer?

396
00:22:37,692 --> 00:22:41,128
I may be gone more than a couple of days.

397
00:22:49,852 --> 00:22:50,921
Nat.

398
00:22:51,012 --> 00:22:52,127
Yes.

399
00:22:53,772 --> 00:22:55,728
I don't know what's happening.

400
00:22:55,812 --> 00:22:57,404
Everything's fine.

401
00:22:58,652 --> 00:23:00,005
I'm handling it.

402
00:23:30,932 --> 00:23:34,208
(Nat) Mr. Rady,
you were Captain Walden's copilot.

403
00:23:34,292 --> 00:23:35,168
That's right.

404
00:23:35,252 --> 00:23:39,006
(Nat) Can you tell me
what you remember about AlKufan?

405
00:23:48,692 --> 00:23:50,171
I remember the earth.

406
00:23:51,972 --> 00:23:55,089
I remember... llario's face.

407
00:23:56,852 --> 00:23:58,649
I wish...

408
00:24:00,372 --> 00:24:04,001
- She hadn't needed to be a hero so bad.
- That's not fair.

409
00:24:04,092 --> 00:24:06,322
We were just doing our job.

410
00:24:06,412 --> 00:24:09,404
It's not Ren's fault I got hit.

411
00:24:09,492 --> 00:24:13,246
She sure as hell saved the lives
of those guys on the Blackhawk.

412
00:24:14,172 --> 00:24:17,289
- You always defend her.
- Why didn't you like her?

413
00:24:17,372 --> 00:24:18,964
She was so butch.

414
00:24:19,052 --> 00:24:20,405
Honey, shut up.

415
00:24:22,412 --> 00:24:24,084
She was, you know.

416
00:24:25,412 --> 00:24:28,324
One of those women
who want to be officers...

417
00:24:28,412 --> 00:24:30,243
Annie, shut up.

418
00:24:32,772 --> 00:24:35,127
She gave her life for those men.

419
00:24:39,372 --> 00:24:40,691
She was a soldier.

420
00:24:56,452 --> 00:24:58,647
There she blows.

421
00:25:06,812 --> 00:25:08,245
(gunfire)

422
00:25:10,052 --> 00:25:12,122
- We're taking fire!
- Holy shit!

423
00:25:18,252 --> 00:25:21,767
- Kill that motherfucker, Bonfires!
- I may as well be pissing on him.

424
00:25:21,852 --> 00:25:24,844
- We need a fucking air strike!
- We got no fucking bomb!

425
00:25:28,692 --> 00:25:30,762
- Making another pass, Ran?
- Yep.

426
00:25:30,852 --> 00:25:34,049
No! We should go for altitude,
and call for support.

427
00:25:34,132 --> 00:25:35,611
After we slow down that tank!

428
00:25:36,212 --> 00:25:39,170
