460
00:27:01,612 --> 00:27:03,409
Mayday! Mayday! This is Dustoff-3!

461
00:27:03,492 --> 00:27:04,402
We are going down!

462
00:27:04,492 --> 00:27:07,882
Mayday! Mayday! This is Dustoff-3!
We're going down! We're going down!

463
00:27:07,972 --> 00:27:09,769
We're going down! Oh, my God...

464
00:27:22,212 --> 00:27:23,201
That's it.

465
00:27:25,172 --> 00:27:28,448
I woke up three days later
on a hospital ship.

466
00:27:28,532 --> 00:27:30,124
Nearly bought it, that's sure.

467
00:27:33,652 --> 00:27:37,611
(Larry King) When did you decide
the type of career in the Army you wanted?

468
00:27:37,692 --> 00:27:42,004
(Schwarzkopf) That happened about
my third year at WestPoint when l was...

469
00:27:42,092 --> 00:27:44,481
l could have gone in the Air Force.

470
00:27:44,572 --> 00:27:46,449
l stood high enough in my class.

471
00:27:46,532 --> 00:27:50,286
You can't get away from that guy.
He's everywhere.

472
00:27:50,372 --> 00:27:53,045
- Hell of a soldier, though.
- You think so?

473
00:27:53,132 --> 00:27:54,531
I know so.

474
00:27:54,612 --> 00:27:56,045
Really. How?

475
00:27:56,132 --> 00:27:58,487
I was with him in the Gulf.

476
00:27:58,572 --> 00:27:59,482
No shit.

477
00:27:59,572 --> 00:28:02,530
