Head down, AItameyer. You might lose it.

612
00:35:46,492 --> 00:35:47,447
You OK, Captain?

613
00:35:47,532 --> 00:35:49,443
Shit in my eye.

614
00:35:49,532 --> 00:35:51,284
Will our guys come tonight?

615
00:35:51,412 --> 00:35:52,731
They’ll be here.

616
00:35:52,812 --> 00:35:54,325
Dust is blowing pretty bad.

617
00:35:54,412 --> 00:35:56,687
I don't know
how much longer Rady can hang on.

618
00:35:56,772 --> 00:35:59,081
I can hear the rag heads
when you're not gabbing.

619
00:35:59,172 --> 00:36:01,049
Then I'd suggest everybody just...

620
00:36:21,132 --> 00:36:22,645
They're going away.

621
00:36:22,732 --> 00:36:24,245
It was just a probe.

622
00:36:24,332 --> 00:36:25,367
llario?

623
00:36:25,452 --> 00:36:26,362
I'm OK.

624
00:36:26,452 --> 00:36:27,362
AItameyer?

625
00:36:27,452 --> 00:36:28,202
My ear!

626
00:36:28,292 --> 00:36:29,247
Monfriez?

627
00:36:29,332 --> 00:36:30,890
I... I took one.

628
00:36:30,972 --> 00:36:35,762
- Rady?
- Hanging in. How about you, Cap?

629
00:36:36,172 --> 00:36:37,127
Unh...

630
00:36:37,212 --> 00:36:39,009
Oh, shit.

631
00:36:39,092 --> 00:36:40,730
Stay with Rady.

632
00:36:46,692 --> 00:36:48,284
I like to come here.

633
00:36:49,532 --> 00:36:52,285
It's not just the bikinis,
although they ain't bad.

634
00:36:52,372 --> 00:36:54,886
It's these kids.

635
00:36:54,972 --> 00:36:56,724
I like to watch them, you know?

636
00:36:56,812 --> 00:36:59,690
My folks had this place
out on Calaveras Lake.

637
00:36:59,772 --> 00:37:02,730
I still go there sometimes, watch 'em dive.

638
00:37:02,812 --> 00:37:04,291
They do the damnedest things.

639
00:37:04,372 --> 00:37:06,727
They never think about the consequences.

640
00:37:08,612 --> 00:37:10,011
Imagine that.

641
00:37:10,092 --> 00:37:13,129
Imagine not thinking
about the consequences?

642
00:37:13,212 --> 00:37:14,884
Imagine that.

643
00:37:18,852 --> 00:37:20,683
Are... are we done?

644
00:37:23,532 --> 00:37:25,727
After the attack...

645
00:37:25,812 --> 00:37:27,609
..during the night...

646
00:37:27,692 --> 00:37:29,569
What?

647
00:37:29,652 --> 00:37:31,085
I mean, we waited.

648
00:37:31,172 --> 00:37:32,525
I... I still don't...

649
00:37:32,612 --> 00:37:37,163
- I... I don't know what you...
- Just go on with what happened.

650
00:37:40,612 --> 00:37:46,369
Well, Karen,...
the captain,... uh, was hurt pretty bad.

651
00:37:47,572 --> 00:37:48,800
Ohh...

652
00:37:48,892 --> 00:37:51,929
Unh...

653
00:37:52,012 --> 00:37:53,889
Unh!

654
00:37:54,892 --> 00:37:56,211
How many rounds left?

655
00:37:56,292 --> 00:37:57,520
Just a sec.

656
00:37:57,612 --> 00:37:58,965
How many rounds?

657
00:37:59,052 --> 00:38:00,883
I just opened my last can of ammo.

658
00:38:01,132 --> 00:38:02,963
Five mags for the M-16,...

659
00:38:03,052 --> 00:38:04,087
..9-mll's full.

660
00:38:04,292 --> 00:38:05,168
Mine's empty.

661
00:38:06,892 --> 00:38:08,450
Fire a couple of rounds off.

662
00:38:08,532 --> 00:38:11,444
- Let 'em know we're still allve.
- Roger that, Captain.

663
00:38:13,252 --> 00:38:16,722
Now save your ammo
for something you can see.

664
00:38:18,852 --> 00:38:23,050
During the course of the incident,
did she display any doubt, any fear...

665
00:38:23,132 --> 00:38:26,442
..when she had to make
these life-and-death decisions?

666
00:38:26,532 --> 00:38:28,284
No.

667
00:38:28,372 --> 00:38:29,646
No. Never.

668
00:38:29,732 --> 00:38:30,881
She just made 'em.

669
00:38:30,972 --> 00:38:32,849
Just like that?

670
00:38:32,932 --> 00:38:34,365
Just like that.

671
00:38:34,452 --> 00:38:37,205
Karen,... the captain... she had this quality.

672
00:38:37,292 --> 00:38:39,806
The heavier the pressure,
the calmer she got.

673
00:38:39,892 --> 00:38:41,644
We knew they were out there,...

674
00:38:41,732 --> 00:38:43,324
..sneaking up on us.

675
00:38:43,412 --> 00:38:46,927
But we also knew
at first light they were going to attack.

676
00:38:47,012 --> 00:38:50,846
I don't know why people think only
good things happen when the sun rises.

677
00:38:51,092 --> 00:38:52,161
Incoming!

678
00:39:02,172 --> 00:39:03,127
How many?

679
00:39:03,212 --> 00:39:04,440
100. Maybe more.

680
00:39:04,532 --> 00:39:06,011
Any good at hand-to-hand?

681
00:39:06,092 --> 00:39:08,287
Wait till they get closer.

682
00:39:08,372 --> 00:39:10,886
Make every round count!

683
00:39:13,892 --> 00:39:15,371
- Shit!
- Quiet!

684
00:39:15,452 --> 00:39:16,931
What in Christ for?

685
00:39:17,012 --> 00:39:18,445
They know we're here!

686
00:39:18,532 --> 00:39:20,409
Quiet! I hear something!

687
00:39:20,492 --> 00:39:21,481
(helicopter)

688
00:39:23,732 --> 00:39:25,563
Choppers!

689
00:39:27,972 --> 00:39:30,202
Hey!

690
00:39:30,292 --> 00:39:33,011
Yeah! Yeah! Yeah!

691
00:39:33,092 --> 00:39:34,684
Go! Go!

692
00:39:34,772 --> 00:39:36,000
Yeah! (laughs)

693
00:39:44,852 --> 00:39:46,171
Let's get out of here!

694
00:39:46,252 --> 00:39:47,241
llario, get the captain!

695
00:39:47,332 --> 00:39:48,685
There's the rescue!

696
00:39:56,052 --> 00:39:58,202
Help Rady!

697
00:39:58,292 --> 00:39:59,850
Pick him up!

698
00:39:59,932 --> 00:40:01,604
Go! Let's go! Let go! Let's go!

699
00:40:03,172 --> 00:40:05,527
Come on! Let's move! Move it!

700
00:40:06,612 --> 00:40:08,011
Gotta go! We gotta go!

701
00:40:08,092 --> 00:40:10,128
Come back for me with a stretcher!

702
00:40:10,212 --> 00:40:11,247
Go!

703
00:40:31,012 --> 00:40:33,162
llario, let's get the fuck outta here!

704
00:40:34,812 --> 00:40:36,643
Get the fuck outta here!

705
00:40:49,532 --> 00:40:50,885
Aah!

706
00:40:51,132 --> 00:40:52,451
Aah!

707
00:40:54,812 --> 00:40:55,801
Medic!

708
00:40:57,852 --> 00:40:59,604
Come on! Get him up!

709
00:41:03,412 --> 00:41:05,448
Move! Come on! Let's go!

710
00:41:09,132 --> 00:41:10,167
Where's Walden?

711
00:41:11,452 --> 00:41:12,965
Captain Walden is dead.

712
00:41:16,412 --> 00:41:19,006
Strike leader, this is Dustoff-6.

713
00:41:19,092 --> 00:41:22,050
We have all the friends.
You're clear and hot.

714
00:41:22,132 --> 00:41:24,692
Roger, Dustoff-6. Going on down.

715
00:41:33,452 --> 00:41:35,363
So...

716
00:41:35,452 --> 00:41:37,807
Is she gonna get it?
Is she gonna get the medal?

717
00:41:37,892 --> 00:41:41,248
Well, I sincerely hope so.

718
00:41:41,332 --> 00:41:44,688
I just... I don't want to tell that story again.

719
00:41:44,772 --> 00:41:46,888
Not one more time.

720
00:41:46,972 --> 00:41:48,564
Yeah, I understand.

721
00:41:50,372 --> 00:41:51,691
May I be excused?

722
00:41:51,772 --> 00:41:53,808
Yes, you can.

723
00:41:53,892 --> 00:41:56,725
Oh, one more thing I'm confused about.

724
00:41:58,172 --> 00:41:59,685
This M-16...

725
00:42:00,972 --> 00:42:01,882
What?

726
00:42:01,972 --> 00:42:03,769
Did it run out of ammo?

727
00:42:05,452 --> 00:42:07,329
Uh, what did I say?

728
00:42:08,612 --> 00:42:11,285
I don't remember. That's why I'm asking.

729
00:42:12,772 --> 00:42:14,410
I guess, uh...

730
00:42:14,492 --> 00:42:18,326
I guess it ran out of ammo
sometime during the morning.

731
00:42:18,412 --> 00:42:20,164
Um...

732
00:42:20,252 --> 00:42:21,844
Or, no, sometime during the night...

733
00:42:21,932 --> 00:42:23,251
I don't know.

734
00:42:23,332 --> 00:42:26,529
See, the Blackhawk crew
said they heard M-16 fire...

735
00:42:26,612 --> 00:42:29,763
..during the rescue that morning.

736
00:42:30,052 --> 00:42:31,724
Did they?

737
00:42:31,812 --> 00:42:34,201
That's right.

738
00:42:34,292 --> 00:42:35,884
Must've been wrong, then.

739
00:42:35,972 --> 00:42:36,882
Them or you?

740
00:42:36,972 --> 00:42:38,371
Who, them or you?

741
00:42:38,452 --> 00:42:39,680
Oh, them. Them, yeah.

742
00:42:39,772 --> 00:42:41,330
No, they must have been wrong.

743
00:42:41,572 --> 00:42:43,290
OK.

744
00:42:44,372 --> 00:42:45,361
OK.

745
00:42:47,052 --> 00:42:48,485
What about the letter?

746
00:42:49,892 --> 00:42:50,802
A what?

747
00:42:50,972 --> 00:42:54,806
You and Walden traded letters to send home
in case anything happened to you.

748
00:42:54,892 --> 00:42:55,961
Oh, yeah. Yes, sir.

749
00:42:56,052 --> 00:42:57,326
So, who was hers to?

750
00:42:57,412 --> 00:42:58,322
Her folks.

751
00:42:58,412 --> 00:43:00,801
- So you sent it?
- Yeah.

752
00:43:00,892 --> 00:43:02,530
Her folks, they're good people.

753
00:43:02,612 --> 00:43:04,443
They got a farm out in Abllene.

754
00:43:04,532 --> 00:43:08,366
They'd come to Hood, look after her kid
while we went out on exercises.

755
00:43:08,452 --> 00:43:10,727
Yeah... Yeah.

756
00:43:12,492 --> 00:43:13,402
OK.

757
00:43:13,492 --> 00:43:15,210
Thank you, Specialist.

758
00:43:15,292 --> 00:43:16,691
Thank you very much, sir.

759
00:43:22,412 --> 00:43:24,289
I read somewhere...

760
00:43:24,372 --> 00:43:27,489
..that if a child doesn't see a person die,...

761
00:43:27,572 --> 00:43:30,530
..or dead, like in a casket,...

762
00:43:30,612 --> 00:43:33,604
..that the person isn't really dead for them.

763
00:43:34,772 --> 00:43:36,490
That'd be nice, wouldn't it?

764
00:43:37,772 --> 00:43:38,761
Yes, ma'am.

765
00:43:40,692 --> 00:43:43,889
It was, uh... unusual, wasn't it,...

766
00:43:43,972 --> 00:43:46,532
..for Karen to want to be a helicopter pilot?

767
00:43:46,612 --> 00:43:48,728
I guess that's my fault.

768
00:43:48,812 --> 00:43:51,042
I took her to the fair when she was 11.

769
00:43:51,132 --> 00:43:54,283
12 - 7th grade.

770
00:43:54,372 --> 00:43:57,045
Anyway, there was a helicopter there.

771
00:43:57,132 --> 00:43:59,123
Small one with a bubble up front.

772
00:43:59,212 --> 00:44:01,680
The fella... the pilot was selling rides.

773
00:44:01,772 --> 00:44:04,366
I bought Karen a ticket.

774
00:44:04,452 --> 00:44:06,488
It was a short ride.

775
00:44:06,572 --> 00:44:09,132
But when she came down...

776
00:44:09,212 --> 00:44:12,010
Well, I don't think
she ever came down, actually.

777
00:44:12,772 --> 00:44:17,323
She showed up
at the dinner table one day,...

778
00:44:17,412 --> 00:44:20,245
..just after she finished TCU.

779
00:44:20,332 --> 00:44:22,163
She's joined the Army.

780
00:44:22,252 --> 00:44:24,004
She wants to fly helicopters.

781
00:44:24,092 --> 00:44:25,605
She's real stubborn about it, too.

782
00:44:25,692 --> 00:44:27,648
That's our Karen, you know, stubborn.

783
00:44:27,732 --> 00:44:29,529
So's Anne Marie here.

784
00:44:32,012 --> 00:44:33,923
Come here, honey.

785
00:44:34,012 --> 00:44:34,967
Excuse me.

786
00:44:41,652 --> 00:44:43,131
Uh, the young men,...

787
00:44:43,212 --> 00:44:46,921
..the ones that came to tell us about Karen...

788
00:44:47,012 --> 00:44:49,480
..they were dressed just like you.

789
00:44:49,572 --> 00:44:52,245
Oh, I see.

