Try.

1036
00:58:38,732 --> 00:58:40,051
Now!

1037
00:58:43,572 --> 00:58:45,483
- Yay!
- Whoo!

1038
00:58:46,572 --> 00:58:48,881
So what happened during the night?

1039
00:58:48,972 --> 00:58:50,485
Walden and llario,...

1040
00:58:50,572 --> 00:58:53,564
..they wouldn't shut up about being rescued.

1041
00:58:55,212 --> 00:58:57,487
Like the Army had nothing else to do.

1042
00:58:57,572 --> 00:58:59,483
Dust is blowing hard out there.

1043
00:58:59,572 --> 00:59:03,326
- Think they’ll find us tonight?
- AWACS lost us when the ADT got hit.

1044
00:59:03,412 --> 00:59:05,926
SOP is for search and rescue
to begin looking...

1045
00:59:06,012 --> 00:59:07,889
Christ, Captain, are you crying?

1046
00:59:07,972 --> 00:59:09,530
It's OK. It's just tension.

1047
00:59:09,612 --> 00:59:12,251
Hey, you're going to be OK, OK?

1048
00:59:12,332 --> 00:59:14,084
They’ll find us. It’ll be OK.

1049
00:59:14,172 --> 00:59:17,881
I can hear the rag heads moving,
as soon as you girls stop gabbing.

1050
00:59:33,572 --> 00:59:35,051
They're going away.

1051
00:59:35,132 --> 00:59:36,451
It was just a probe.

1052
00:59:36,532 --> 00:59:38,727
- Shit!
- I'm OK.

1053
00:59:38,812 --> 00:59:40,564
- (Monfriez) I took one.
- How's Rady?

1054
00:59:40,652 --> 00:59:43,120
Hanging in. Captain?

1055
00:59:44,212 --> 00:59:46,680
Ah! Oh!

1056
00:59:49,052 --> 00:59:52,203
So the rest of the night
went without incident?

1057
00:59:53,892 --> 00:59:55,007
Yeah.

1058
00:59:55,092 --> 00:59:56,923
Wasn't that enough for one night?

1059
00:59:58,012 --> 00:59:59,968
You want to continue this tomorrow?

1060
01:00:02,372 --> 01:00:04,442
I don't get emotional about this shit.

1061
01:00:04,532 --> 01:00:06,090
I've been there, you know?

1062
01:00:07,532 --> 01:00:09,363
OK. Go on.

1063
01:00:09,452 --> 01:00:12,410
Well, after the firefight, we argued mainly.

1064
01:00:12,492 --> 01:00:17,088
llario was freaked out by the dark, and
Walden wanted to surrender at first light.

1065
01:00:17,852 --> 01:00:21,640
She was a wreck, kept asking about
the ammo, worrying we didn't have enough.

1066
01:00:21,732 --> 01:00:23,529
I knew they'd attack at dawn.

1067
01:00:25,412 --> 01:00:28,324
So what happened during the evacuation?

1068
01:00:29,812 --> 01:00:31,325
Evacuation.

1069
01:00:32,852 --> 01:00:34,046
(gunfire)

1070
01:00:35,492 --> 01:00:36,971
All right, let's go.

1071
01:00:37,052 --> 01:00:38,326
There's the rescue.

1072
01:00:41,892 --> 01:00:44,247
AItameyer, give me a hand with Rady.

1073
01:00:45,812 --> 01:00:47,211
- Come on, Captain!
- Ow!

1074
01:00:47,292 --> 01:00:48,202
Come on!

1075
01:00:48,292 --> 01:00:49,327
- No! Don't move me!
- Get away!

1076
01:00:49,412 --> 01:00:50,481
Suck it up!

1077
01:00:50,572 --> 01:00:52,802
I got you covered! Ready?

1078
01:00:55,372 --> 01:00:56,441
Go! Go! Go!

1079
01:00:58,612 --> 01:01:01,080
- llario, move!
- Not without the Captain!

1080
01:01:01,172 --> 01:01:02,446
I’ll get her.

1081
01:01:02,532 --> 01:01:04,762
No! I'm not leaving!

1082
01:01:04,852 --> 01:01:07,241
I'm not leaving! It's not safe!

1083
01:01:07,332 --> 01:01:10,051
They're taking fire!
The choppers are waiting!

1084
01:01:10,132 --> 01:01:11,690
No! No! No!

1085
01:01:21,692 --> 01:01:23,410
Get the fuck outta here!

1086
01:01:26,012 --> 01:01:27,365
Come on!

1087
01:01:29,012 --> 01:01:30,365
She fired at you?

1088
01:01:30,452 --> 01:01:31,726
Near us, yeah.

1089
01:01:31,812 --> 01:01:36,124
Then why did you lie to the investigators
about how she performed?

1090
01:01:37,852 --> 01:01:41,561
They'd already put together
their own bullshit version of the story...

1091
01:01:41,652 --> 01:01:45,850
..before they talked to me. I told them
what they wanted to hear. We all did.

1092
01:01:45,932 --> 01:01:51,404
But that's the truth, so forget about the
medal, or leave it as it is. I don't give a fuck.

1093
01:01:51,492 --> 01:01:55,770
So nobody from your Huey crew
fired an M-16 any time during the rescue?

1094
01:01:55,852 --> 01:01:57,410
That's affirmed, sir.

1095
01:01:57,492 --> 01:01:58,811
Monfriez, you ready?

1096
01:02:02,172 --> 01:02:03,571
You sure about that?

1097
01:02:03,652 --> 01:02:06,212
That's affirmative, sir.

1098
01:02:06,292 --> 01:02:07,850
We had no ammo.

1099
01:02:13,372 --> 01:02:14,691
So how about it, Colonel?

1100
01:02:14,772 --> 01:02:16,649
Want to go a few rounds?

1101
01:02:16,732 --> 01:02:18,768
Are you threatening me, soldier?

1102
01:02:18,852 --> 01:02:21,161
- Where's your brain bucket?
- I don't need it.

1103
01:02:21,252 --> 01:02:22,844
Don't step in here without one.

1104
01:02:22,932 --> 01:02:27,528
I have to tell you again,
you won't have a head to stick it on.

1105
01:02:27,612 --> 01:02:30,331
Come on, Jersey. Right here.

1106
01:02:30,412 --> 01:02:31,731
Let's see what you got.

1107
01:02:31,812 --> 01:02:33,609
You got nothing, man.

1108
01:02:34,692 --> 01:02:36,125
Come on!

1109
01:02:43,692 --> 01:02:45,887
(ringing tone)

1110
01:02:45,972 --> 01:02:48,088
- (Meredith) Hello.
- Hello? Baby?

1111
01:02:48,172 --> 01:02:49,446
How're you doing?

1112
01:02:49,532 --> 01:02:51,170
Hi.

1113
01:02:54,252 --> 01:02:55,924
How',s it going?

1114
01:02:56,012 --> 01:02:57,331
Outstanding.

1115
01:02:58,532 --> 01:02:59,681
Outstanding.

1116
01:02:59,772 --> 01:03:02,366
I was calling, I wondered...

1117
01:03:02,452 --> 01:03:03,680
What... what kind of...

1118
01:03:03,772 --> 01:03:05,649
What size T-shirts the kids wear?

1119
01:03:05,732 --> 01:03:07,688
I want to get the kids some T-shirts.

1120
01:03:09,452 --> 01:03:11,807
You know their sizes as well as I do.

1121
01:03:11,892 --> 01:03:13,723
Are you OK?

1122
01:03:15,132 --> 01:03:16,121
Nat?

1123
01:03:18,212 --> 01:03:20,772
I got a pint of, um...

1124
01:03:20,852 --> 01:03:22,968
..Scotch here in a paper bag.

1125
01:03:24,652 --> 01:03:26,483
I don't want to drink any of it.

1126
01:03:28,492 --> 01:03:30,562
Can you tell me why you need it?

1127
01:03:36,732 --> 01:03:39,246
Want me to prattle on for a minute?
I can do that.

1128
01:03:39,332 --> 01:03:40,242
(Nat) Please.

1129
01:03:40,332 --> 01:03:43,085
OK. Um...

1130
01:03:43,172 --> 01:03:44,605
The new refrigerator doesn't work.

1131
01:03:44,692 --> 01:03:46,922
The light doesn't come on
when you open the door.

1132
01:03:47,012 --> 01:03:51,881
I had to drive all the way
over to Wagner, 12 blocks,...

1133
01:03:51,972 --> 01:03:54,770
..just so that Brian could practice
riding his bike.

1134
01:03:54,852 --> 01:03:57,082
He's afraid of falling in front of his friends.

1135
01:03:58,852 --> 01:04:02,288
He refuses to let anyone
see him riding with training wheels.

1136
01:04:03,812 --> 01:04:07,725
They've both taken to sleeping in our bed
since you left.

1137
01:04:09,052 --> 01:04:11,407
It's like sleeping between two tornadoes.

1138
01:04:11,492 --> 01:04:13,164
I better go, baby.

1139
01:04:13,252 --> 01:04:14,605
Don Boylar called.

1140
01:04:14,692 --> 01:04:16,045
Jesus.

1141
01:04:17,252 --> 01:04:18,526
I better go.

1142
01:04:18,612 --> 01:04:21,046
- Nat, talk to me.
- I can't.

1143
01:04:21,132 --> 01:04:22,611
- Why not?
- I can't!

1144
01:04:22,692 --> 01:04:24,683
Bullshit. Bull! Talk to me!

1145
01:04:27,052 --> 01:04:28,644
(dialing tone)

1146
01:04:32,172 --> 01:04:33,605
Oh, Christ.

1147
01:04:34,972 --> 01:04:35,882
Colonel?

1148
01:04:35,972 --> 01:04:37,371
Colonel?

1149
01:04:45,532 --> 01:04:47,648
Can we get some coffee, please?

1150
01:04:51,732 --> 01:04:53,245
You're not a happy man.

1151
01:04:54,532 --> 01:04:56,921
A woman? The Army?

1152
01:04:57,012 --> 01:04:58,081
AI Bathra?

1153
01:05:09,492 --> 01:05:11,164
Talk to me.

1154
01:05:11,252 --> 01:05:12,970
Off the record, if you want.

1155
01:05:13,052 --> 01:05:14,405
Way, way off the record.

1156
01:05:14,492 --> 01:05:15,925
Rangers' honour.

1157
01:05:18,332 --> 01:05:19,321
Serling,...

1158
01:05:21,355 --> 01:05:22,868
How long you been back?

1159
01:05:24,795 --> 01:05:25,989
Six months.

1160
01:05:26,075 --> 01:05:28,543
And you...
you've been in the service how long?

1161
01:05:28,635 --> 01:05:29,863
17 years.

1162
01:05:29,955 --> 01:05:33,152
Ah, they got me running this inquiry...

1163
01:05:33,235 --> 01:05:35,908
..on this girl pilot.

1164
01:05:35,995 --> 01:05:37,428
Captain Karen Walden.

1165
01:05:37,515 --> 01:05:41,793
She’ll be the first woman
to get the Medal of Honour for combat.

1166
01:05:41,875 --> 01:05:42,671
Oh, boy.

1167
01:05:42,755 --> 01:05:46,191
And everybody in the beltway
wants a piece of this one, right?

1168
01:05:47,635 --> 01:05:49,990
I just want to get something clear.

1169
01:05:50,075 --> 01:05:52,635
This time, just want somebody to be a hero.

1170
01:05:53,875 --> 01:05:55,672
I want to get something right.

1171
01:05:55,755 --> 01:05:56,665
Yeah.

1172
01:05:56,755 --> 01:05:59,223
Cos AI Bathra, you know...

1173
01:06:04,315 --> 01:06:05,225
AI Bathra.

1174
01:06:05,315 --> 01:06:07,226
You talked to Boylar's parents?

1175
01:06:07,315 --> 01:06:08,384
Yeah.

1176
01:06:08,475 --> 01:06:09,988
Do they know?

1177
01:06:10,955 --> 01:06:13,185
They heard from a few of his friends.

1178
01:06:13,275 --> 01:06:16,233
Aw, Jesus...

1179
01:06:16,315 --> 01:06:17,304
You know...

1180
01:06:18,875 --> 01:06:21,912
They told Boylar's parents
he died from enemy fire.

1181
01:06:21,995 --> 01:06:23,713
I told them that.

1182
01:06:23,795 --> 01:06:26,946
I carried the message,
went to the funeral,...

1183
01:06:27,035 --> 01:06:29,390
..watched his mother cry her eyes out.

1184
01:06:29,475 --> 01:06:32,194
I stood there
and looked his father in the eye...

1185
01:06:32,275 --> 01:06:35,631
..and told him
his son died brave under fire.

1186
01:06:35,715 --> 01:06:38,912
And I was the one
who gave the order to fire.

1187
01:06:38,995 --> 01:06:40,474
I did it.

1188
01:06:40,555 --> 01:06:43,433
Then the Army gave me a medal...

1189
01:06:43,515 --> 01:06:45,665
..for bravery and valour.

1190
01:06:47,115 --> 01:06:49,709
Then they buried me...

1191
01:06:49,795 --> 01:06:51,114
..in medals.

1192
01:06:52,595 --> 01:06:54,506
Got a sense of humour, don't they?

1193
01:06:58,715 --> 01:07:00,307
Yeah.

1194
01:07:01,795 --> 01:07:05,185
Can't remember anything else
except being in the Army.

1195
01:07:06,635 --> 01:07:10,230
Either being in it or wanting to be in it.

1196
01:07:13,435 --> 01:07:14,868
It's all I know.

1197
01:07:20,315 --> 01:07:21,953
Look, you need to sleep.

1198
01:07:22,035 --> 01:07:23,263
You call me any time.

1199
01:07:23,355 --> 01:07:27,268
Anything you want to say about anything,
on or off the record.

1200
01:07:28,675 --> 01:07:30,950
I'm going to leave you alone for a while.

1201
01:07:36,915 --> 01:07:41,750
llario. Are you saying you can't find him,
or that he's absent without leave?

1202
01:07:41,835 --> 01:07:43,632
(man) Sir, that’s an l... l...

1203
01:07:43,715 --> 01:07:45,467
That's right, specialist llario.

1204
01:07:45,555 --> 01:07:47,432
Well, we contacted the MPs, sir...

1205
01:07:47,515 --> 01:07:49,506
Roger.

1206
01:07:49,595 --> 01:07:51,074
Roger that.

1207
01:07:51,235 --> 01:07:52,953
Thank you.

1208
01:07:53,035 --> 01:07:57,506
Did she display fear when she had
to make these life-and-death decisions?

1209
01:07:57,595 --> 01:08:00,063
(llario) No, never.

1210
01:08:00,155 --> 01:08:03,192
Karen,... the captain... she had this quality.

1211
01:08:03,275 --> 01:08:05,152
The heavier the pressure,
the calmer she got.

1212
01:08:05,235 --> 01:08:09,228
And she... you know, she put up
with a lot of shit to become an officer.

1213
01:08:09,675 --> 01:08:13,634
Had to work twice as hard
as everybody else, be twice as good.

1214
01:08:13,715 --> 01:08:17,071
She’d never let the guard down,
show any sign of weakness.

1215
01:08:17,155 --> 01:08:20,227
But she was tough. She could handle it.

1216
01:08:20,315 --> 01:08:23,591
So, ladies and gentlemen,
what I have to say to you in closing...

1217
01:08:23,675 --> 01:08:25,427
..is to go forth,...

1218
01:08:25,515 --> 01:08:27,631
..to command wisely,...

1219
01:08:27,715 --> 01:08:29,433
..to advise prudently,...

1220
01:08:29,515 --> 01:08:31,551
..to protect with vigilance...

1221
01:08:31,635 --> 01:08:33,990
..and to judge with care.

1222
01:08:34,075 --> 01:08:36,305
And above all,...

1223
01:08:36,395 --> 01:08:39,751
..to defend with all your heart,
all your soul...

1224
01:08:39,835 --> 01:08:41,712
..and all your courage...

1225
01:08:41,795 --> 01:08:45,674
..the lives of the men and women
under your command,...

1226
01:08:45,755 --> 01:08:47,950
..and the United States of America.

1227
01:08:49,995 --> 01:08:53,590
Are you now saying
you’ll report against her getting the medal?

1228
01:08:53,675 --> 01:08:57,270
As I explained to the White House,
there should be a further investigation...

1229
01:08:57,355 --> 01:08:58,993
..before we move forward.
The discrepancies...

1230
01:08:59,075 --> 01:09:01,873
Another matter completely.
Write up a second report.

1231
01:09:01,955 --> 01:09:03,434
That's my point, sir!

1232
01:09:03,515 --> 01:09:05,790
llario's disappeared. Altameyer's missing.

1233
01:09:05,875 --> 01:09:08,343
- Who?
- AItameyer, sir. Walden's crew chief.

1234
01:09:08,435 --> 01:09:10,266
VA hospital's transferred him out
three weeks ago.

1235
01:09:10,355 --> 01:09:11,913
Paperwork's missing.

1236
01:09:11,995 --> 01:09:13,394
Doesn't he have any family?

1237
01:09:13,475 --> 01:09:14,430
Negative.

1238
01:09:14,515 --> 01:09:16,187
Fucking VA. We can't wait, Nat.

1239
01:09:16,275 --> 01:09:19,392
You cannot imagine
the kind of heat I'm getting on this.

1240
01:09:19,475 --> 01:09:20,954
Everybody wants it.

1241
01:09:21,035 --> 01:09:25,904
Senators, congressmen, one shiny
piece of something for people to believe in.

1242
01:09:27,035 --> 01:09:28,263
Whole episode.

1243
01:09:28,355 --> 01:09:29,868
Walden or AI Bathra?

1244
01:09:29,955 --> 01:09:31,434
Both, damn it, both.

1245
01:09:32,195 --> 01:09:33,423
Submit your report today.

1246
01:09:33,555 --> 01:09:34,544
I'm sorry, sir.

1247
01:09:36,435 --> 01:09:39,029
I won't put my name
on an incomplete report.

1248
01:09:39,115 --> 01:09:42,790
May I remind you who recommended you
for this when no-one else 'd touch you?

1249
01:09:42,875 --> 01:09:45,708
You saying you chose me
because I wouldn't rock the boat?

1250
01:09:45,795 --> 01:09:49,344
Dereliction of duty,
drunk and disorderly, conduct unbecoming.

1251
01:09:49,435 --> 01:09:50,914
At best, a dishonorable discharge.

1252
01:09:50,995 --> 01:09:53,953
At worst, AI Bathra gives us
plenty of grounds, if we want 'em.

1253
01:09:54,035 --> 01:09:56,868
At least somebody has finally said it.

1254
01:09:56,955 --> 01:10:00,789
Nat, don't do this. I could give you
a direct order to submit your report.

1255
01:10:00,875 --> 01:10:02,103
Yes, you could.

1256
01:10:10,115 --> 01:10:12,629
Put Hillerman back on the Walden file!

1257
01:10:12,755 --> 01:10:15,906
I handed this to you, Nat, as a way back.

1258
01:10:15,995 --> 01:10:18,111
You could've had one hell of a career.

1259
01:10:19,595 --> 01:10:21,790
And you give Meredith my best.

1260
01:10:21,875 --> 01:10:23,945
Tell her I didn't have any choice.

1261
01:10:24,035 --> 01:10:27,425
I'm going to finish this report.

1262
01:10:27,515 --> 01:10:28,994
On my own, if I have to.

1263
01:10:29,075 --> 01:10:32,306
I'm going to get this one right.

1264
01:10:43,715 --> 01:10:44,943
You want one?

1265
01:10:45,035 --> 01:10:46,468
No, thank you.

1266
01:10:46,555 --> 01:10:51,675
Why is it people never want to eat
when they got something important to say?

1267
01:10:51,755 --> 01:10:54,030
I always want to eat.

1268
01:10:57,115 --> 01:10:59,868
Need you to help me find somebody.

1269
01:10:59,955 --> 01:11:01,468
You want my help?

1270
01:11:01,555 --> 01:11:04,308
Yeah.
Name's AItameyer. Steven AItameyer.

1271
01:11:05,195 --> 01:11:09,268
He was the crew chief on the medevac
chopper, piloted by Karen Walden.

1272
01:11:09,355 --> 01:11:12,711
- One supposed to get a Medal of Honour?
- The very one.

1273
01:11:12,795 --> 01:11:17,186
- The Army's usually tidy about its people.
- Yeah, usually, but not this time.

1274
01:11:18,235 --> 01:11:21,944
First he demobbed,
then they had him in a VA hospital.

1275
01:11:22,035 --> 01:11:25,027
They transferred him.
Now no-one can find him.

1276
01:11:25,115 --> 01:11:26,787
Why do you need me?

1277
01:11:26,875 --> 01:11:29,389
Can't someone in the Pentagon help?

1278
01:11:29,475 --> 01:11:31,193
I'm out of the loop.

1279
01:11:31,275 --> 01:11:33,072
Somebody pissed at you?

1280
01:11:35,515 --> 01:11:38,188
- I'm out of the loop.
- Somebody important?

1281
01:11:38,275 --> 01:11:40,789
- You want to help me or not?
- Hey, who called who here?

1282
01:11:43,395 --> 01:11:44,828
Yeah, sure, I’ll help.

1283
01:11:44,915 --> 01:11:46,906
Just tell me why I'm doing it.

1284
01:11:46,995 --> 01:11:50,305
When you go after stories,
you want them to be right, yes?

1285
01:11:50,395 --> 01:11:51,305
Yeah.

1286
01:11:51,395 --> 01:11:52,384
So do I.

1287
01:11:53,395 --> 01:11:54,908
OK.

1288
